column5: these 2 thing go great together anyone else headed to RICE this weekend for the eyes?

I won't be out this weekend, but I spend a lot of time fishing eyes on rice for sure. The lauunch is 10 mins from my front door, so evenings after work during the week you'll find me out there. See you on the water  S.
i'll be going.  right now saturday looks better weather wise than sunday.  I'll figure out which day or days friday night
Next weekend,4 days staying near Hastings.
With my brother getting his new boat tomorrow we may hit a weekend up there soon.  Curious how y'all will do and good luck.
Ill be out. Me and my son will be heading in saturday morning bright and early... also cant wait.
Is walleye open in zone 17 this weekend? Call me stupid as im on the Trent river ad have no idea...lol ill be up this weekend for the first time since November..LOOONG over due Yikes
Just finished tweaking the kayak for this springs first trip Saturday. Try not to run me over while your out there but feel free to stop by and say hello
Anyone gonna be on the water tonight?

Well me and my son made it out this morn. Within a half hour he had a fairly decent sized muskie to the boat before the line broke. Not long after he pulled in a nice pickeral, followed by a small bass that popped off at the boat. I only had a couple bites. It was choppy and cool with some strong winds but its always nice to get out on the first day.
Went out saturday morning. Winds pretty strong and water was rough. Caught some perch, no walleye
Started at 9 fished till 3 landed 11with 10 in slot 1 over.
Fished Sunday from 7-4 3 guys 1 walleye, couldnt fish a single spot I normally hit because of the wind. It was 1 of the roughest days Ive spent on the water, did manage a boat full of hail lol.
same here i was out all day sat .... not eye at all  nothing like last year

My brother, is taking my father who has parkinsons to the tower manor lodge next week for a weeks holiday.   I am wondering if anyone could give me a few pointers to pass on to my dad and brother to get them started. My brother has a 19ft boat and is taking it with him. They will also have a my brothers young kids with them so a panfish spot would be great to know also. Thanks for your help if your interested. I have never been there so I am no help whatsoever. Matt
Find a weedline in 8-10 fow and rip bucktails along it, and throw cranks along the line.
+1  Last time I was out they were hitting eerie deeries tipped with a piece of worm.
